<div id="review_3653999334" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3653999334" />
    <a title="Sasa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2720159-sasa"><img alt="Sasa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1604367510p2/2720159.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3653999334?book_show_action=true">Jun 08, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sasa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sasa" href="/user/show/2720159-sasa">Sasa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781534441934" href="/book/show/54238295-a-pho-love-story">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2720159-sasa?shelf=author-of-color">author-of-color</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2720159-sasa?shelf=cw-sexism">cw-sexism</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2720159-sasa?shelf=young-adult">young-adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2720159-sasa?shelf=war-military">war-military</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2720159-sasa?shelf=cw-diaspora">cw-diaspora</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2720159-sasa?shelf=food">food</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2720159-sasa?shelf=trope-unrequited">trope-unrequited</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2720159-sasa?shelf=own-voices">own-voices</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2720159-sasa?shelf=south-southeast-asian">south-southeast-asian</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2720159-sasa?shelf=favorite-covers">favorite-covers</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3653999334" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13313778008643493897">4.5<br/><br/>I am so glad this book exists. Teenage me would have appreciated this book so, so much and it would have been crucial to her journey of self-love. Adult me still really appreciates this book&apos;s existence and how unapologetically Vietnamese it is, from using Viber to having <i>Paris By Night</i> in the background, but there are a lot of YA contemporary tropes and emotional teenage meandering that I didn&apos;t care for. That&apos;s just a personal thing and is not a strike against the novel overall. Every sense</span>
  <span id="freeText13313778008643493897" style="display:none">4.5<br /><br />I am so glad this book exists. Teenage me would have appreciated this book so, so much and it would have been crucial to her journey of self-love. Adult me still really appreciates this book's existence and how unapologetically Vietnamese it is, from using Viber to having <i>Paris By Night</i> in the background, but there are a lot of YA contemporary tropes and emotional teenage meandering that I didn't care for. That's just a personal thing and is not a strike against the novel overall. Every sense was stimulated by this book—I got to feel Linh's love for art (an interest I also share), I could taste and smell every single food and drink that was mentioned, I got to brush up on my Vietnamese, I could see the same trauma the characters saw on their parents' faces reflected in my own parents during their escape from the war—it's like this book was made for me and I cannot thank Loan Le enough for creating it. I hope she continues and that more Vietnamese authors can get the same opportunities.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13313778008643493897" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

